  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Death, non-fatal MI, non-fatal stroke, recurrent angina, emergency room (ER) visit due to any CV-related diseases or readmission due to any CV-related diseases confirmed by the physicians.</measure>
    <time_frame>one year</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>BP, lipid, glucose, EBM drugs and self-care efficacy</measure>
    <time_frame>one year</time_frame>
    <description>Blood pressure &lt; 140/90 mmHg (&lt; 130/80 mmHg in the diabetics and patients with chronic kidney disease)
Hypercholesterolemia：LDL &lt; 100 mg/dl
Diabetic：HbA1c &lt; 7%
Smoking cessation rate
Adherence rate of EBM medication including anti-platelet agent, beta-blocker, RAS blocker and lipid-lowering agent.
Efficacy of self care</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
